#!/usr/bin/env perl
use warnings;
use strict;

use feature 'say';

use lib './lib';

use Gentoo::App::Pram;

Gentoo::App::Pram->run(\@ARGV);

__END__

=head1 NAME

pram - Fetch a Github pull request as an am-like patch and apply it onto HEAD
of the current git repository.

=head1 DESCRIPTION

pram is a frontend script to the Gentoo::App::Pram module. This script helps
you fetch pull requests from Github's CDN as an am-like patch. To facilitate
the closing of pull requests, the script automatically adds a "Closes:" header
to each commit contained in the PR. The patch in question will then appear in
your favourite editor for a final review.  The script eventually asks whether
the patch is to be applied onto HEAD of the current git repository. If not, the
patch is deleted.

=head1 SYNOPSIS

pram <pull request number>

 --repository|r <repository>   Set repository to fetch PR from to <repository>.
 --editor|e     <editor>       Set editor to visualise patch in to <editor>.
 --help|h                      Display help.
 --man|m                       Display a man page.

=head1 EXAMPLE

 # This command will fetch PR 123 from the GitHub repository 'monsieurp/gentools'
 # and display it in emacs.
 $ pram --editor emacs --repository monsieurp/gentools 123

=head1 AUTHOR

Patrice Clement <monsieurp@gentoo.org>

=cut
